his own early practice.

91
00:05:14,040 --> 00:05:16,720
'Ey up - I can spy another rig.

92
00:05:21,680 --> 00:05:23,399
Not that it mattered.

93
00:05:23,400 --> 00:05:25,360
BLEEP! Where's the brake pedal?
Sh...

94
00:05:27,320 --> 00:05:29,240
Bit sharp on the brake, but...

95
00:05:33,640 --> 00:05:37,399
What did matter,
now we were all together,

96
00:05:37,400 --> 00:05:41,759
were a couple of crucial bits
of trucking business.

97
00:05:41,760 --> 00:05:45,239
Right, now, before we go,
I've got a little app on me phone

98
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:49,320
for your official CB call name,
your trucker name.

99
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:52,279
OK, Chris, we'll start with you.

100
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:55,120
So it's your initials, CH,
so C...

101
00:05:57,040 --> 00:05:59,639
..Chopper!

102
00:05:59,640 --> 00:06:02,319
H... Hog.

103
00:06:02,320 --> 00:06:06,359
Chopper Hog. That's you.

104
00:06:06,360 --> 00:06:09,279
Right, here's mine. P...

105
00:06:09,280 --> 00:06:10,520
..Professor.

106
00:06:12,960 --> 00:06:15,759
Moose. Professor Moose.

107
00:06:15,760 --> 00:06:18,039
Right, Fred, now I'm gonna give you
the option here.

108
00:06:18,040 --> 00:06:20,319
Do you wanna start with F or A?

109
00:06:20,320 --> 00:06:23,719
Let's try A first.
I'll go for me Sunday name, Andrew.

110
00:06:23,720 --> 00:06:25,719
Admiral.

111
00:06:25,720 --> 00:06:27,360
I chose well.

112
00:06:29,040 --> 00:06:30,480
F...

113
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:35,280
So you are Admiral Fiddler.

114
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:41,199
I am not having that.
I am not having that!

115
00:06:41,200 --> 00:06:45,479
You've just made
my entire year, McGuinness.

116
00:06:45,480 --> 00:06:47,719
Admiral Fiddler!

117
00:06:47,720 --> 00:06:49,080
No!

118
00:06:51,560 --> 00:06:56,319
Official naming ceremony done with,
next on the trucking to-do list

119
00:06:56,320 --> 00:06:59,280
was the obligatory drag race.

120
00:07:01,080 --> 00:07:05,159
And since Sean Taylor also seemed
to be a racing enthusiast,

121
00:07:05,160 --> 00:07:08,079
Harris had to perform.

122
00:07:08,080 --> 00:07:10,559
Now, my brief experience
of this vehicle,

123
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:12,239
I was told not to hurry
the gearbox.

124
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:15,799
I'm gonna be slow gear shifts,
and use the torque.

125
00:07:15,800 --> 00:07:17,560
STARTER: Standing by.

126
00:07:19,600 --> 00:07:24,879
In three, two, one...

127
00:07:24,880 --> 00:07:28,079
I've stalled it. I've stalled it.

128
00:07:28,080 --> 00:07:29,640
Oh-ho!

129
00:07:31,920 --> 00:07:38,240
STARTER: Standing by to go
in three, two, one.

130
00:07:40,240 --> 00:07:41,320
Go!

131
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:47,999
Yeah! Here we go.

132
00:07:48,000 --> 00:07:49,760
Oh! We've done 'em!

133
00:07:50,920 --> 00:07:52,559
Oh, Paddy's off.

134
00:07:52,560 --> 00:07:54,559
Breaker one-nine. Breaker one-nine.

135
00:07:54,560 --> 00:07:56,400
We've got a big rubber duck.

136
00:07:57,960 --> 00:07:59,319
FREDDIE'S ENGINE SPLUTTERS

137
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:01,799
Ooh, that's not right.

138
00:08:01,800 --> 00:08:03,279
Oh!

139
00:08:03,280 --> 00:08:06,320
He's got... McGuinness has got
a much bigger engine than me.

140
00:08:08,160 --> 00:08:10,439
What is going on here?

141
00:08:10,440 --> 00:08:12,919
I'm coming up on Paddy now.

142
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:15,119
Oh! Yeah, we're going, we're going,
we're going!

143
00:08:15,120 --> 00:08:18,560
A bit too soon, Fred.
Watch me go, boys! Look at this!

144
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:22,199
Oh, God, no! He's back on me!

145
00:08:22,200 --> 00:08:23,560
Damn you, Harris!

146
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:27,280
Oh-ho-ho! Ho-ho-ho-ho!

147
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:31,000
Oh, I was in the wrong gear!

148
00:08:32,680 --> 00:08:35,519
We're flying, me and the Scania.

149
00:08:35,520 --> 00:08:37,759
Come on! Come on!

150
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:41,279
Not a chance, Fiddler.
Not a chance.

151
00:08:41,280 --> 00:08:43,440
Admiral, it is. Admiral!

152
00:08:45,040 --> 00:08:48,360
Look at that!
It's a massive victory!

153
00:08:51,960 --> 00:08:56,519
Well, lads, I don't know what to
say. That was an annihilation.

154
00:08:56,520 --> 00:08:58,839
Did you stall on the line, Paddy?
I can't remember.

155
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:00,559
Did you? Was it you or was it Chris?

156
00:09:00,560 --> 00:09:02,839
Yeah, I don't think I stalled.
Did you stall, Fred?

157
00:09:02,840 --> 00:09:05,080
No, I didn't.
I just got in it and did it!

158
00:09:08,560 --> 00:09:12,079
Now, if you're thinking that,
in the world of HGVs,

159
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:15,439
a drag race is about
as irrelevant as it gets,

160
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:20,639
then it's just as well this next bit
was much more important.

161
00:09:20,640 --> 00:09:21,999
Horn.

162
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:26,159
I wanna hear your horns.
Let's go, lads. Fred horn first.

163
00:09:26,160 --> 00:09:28,359
DEEP BLAST

164
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:29,399
It's like the QE2.

165
00:09:29,400 --> 00:09:31,999
HORN CONTINUES

166
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,400
McGuinness, let's hear yours.

167
00:09:34,760 --> 00:09:36,279
DAINTY TOOT

168
00:09:36,280 --> 00:09:38,879
What's that?! What's that? "Meep!"

169
00:09:38,880 --> 00:09:40,159
PADDY TOOTS

170
00:09:40,160 --> 00:09:42,439
Gotta be honest,
that's ruined the day for me.

171
00:09:42,440 --> 00:09:44,639
Right, lads, here we go.

172
00:09:44,640 --> 00:09:46,439
LOUD, MELODIC BLARE

173
00:09:46,440 --> 00:09:47,799
Oh!

174
00:09:47,800 --> 00:09:50,000
HORN CONTINUES

175
00:09:52,200 --> 00:09:54,159
That's proper!

176
00:09:54,160 --> 00:09:56,639
FREDDIE GROANS

177
00:09:56,640 --> 00:09:59,439
And to make sure we'd turned over
every page

178
00:09:59,440 --> 00:10:04,240
of the HGV driver's playbook,
we still needed to test precision.

179
00:10:05,000 --> 00:10:07,919
So, in the time it took
to lay out a few cones,

180
00:10:07,920 --> 00:10:10,960
we had ourselves
a reversing race.

181
00:10:12,720 --> 00:10:16,479
First to back up into their bay
is king of the big rigs.

182
00:10:16,480 --> 00:10:18,159
STARTER: Three, two...
Come on.

183
00:10:18,160 --> 00:10:20,400
...one, go.

184
00:10:26,480 --> 00:10:27,920
Oh, oh, oh.

185
00:10:30,960 --> 00:10:32,360
Right, we've got this.

186
00:10:34,440 --> 00:10:35,560
Here we go.

187
00:10:36,840 --> 00:10:38,319
Straight back.

188
00:10:38,320 --> 00:10:40,039
I can't really see
down the side of it.

189
00:10:40,040 --> 00:10:41,400
I'm making the turn.

190
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:47,359
Left hand down.
Left hand down.

191
00:10:47,360 --> 00:10:50,039
Ho-ho-ho. This is tricky!

192
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:51,599
Oh, God. I'm all over the place.

193
00:10:51,600 --> 00:10:53,480
I'm gonna go forwards again.

194
00:10:54,560 --> 00:10:56,639
Whoa!

195
00:10:56,640 --> 00:10:58,279
You've cut me off, Fred.

196
00:10:58,280 --> 00:10:59,519
I can promise you

197
00:10:59,520 --> 00:11:02,039
it's not intentional.

198
00:11:02,040 --> 00:11:05,439
I'll straighten it out.
This is awful!

199
00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:08,919
Come on. Come on, Harris.

200
00:11:08,920 --> 00:11:10,680
PADDY: You're in my bay,
you clown.

201
00:11:11,680 --> 00:11:12,920
CHRIS LAUGHS

202
00:11:14,120 --> 00:11:16,119
Come on. Come on.

203
00:11:16,120 --> 00:11:18,159
Get out of me bay!

204
00:11:18,160 --> 00:11:19,839
I'm in, I'm in.

205
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:21,239
I'm in.

206
00:11:21,240 --> 00:11:23,599
I'm in. I'm in. I'm in, boys!

207
00:11:23,600 --> 00:11:26,279
How am I supposed to get in?

208
00:11:26,280 --> 00:11:28,079
It doesn't matter
cos I've already won.

209
00:11:28,080 --> 00:11:31,599
You've won because I've had
to wait cos that...

210
00:11:31,600 --> 00:11:35,519
...gormless get cut me off
and then went in my bay!

211
00:11:35,520 --> 00:11:37,360
DEEP HORN BLAST

212
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:43,479
I'm blocking him in.

213
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:45,680
LOUD, COMMANDING HORN

214
00:11:47,520 --> 00:11:50,879
I tell you, you'd be causing
murder at Moto services,

215
00:11:50,880 --> 00:11:52,199
you here, Paddy.

216
00:11:52,200 --> 00:11:54,759
You OK, Patrick?

217
00:11:54,760 --> 00:11:56,759
That'll teach you
for taking my bay!

218
00:11:56,760 --> 00:11:58,159
What's happened?

219
00:11:58,160 --> 00:12:00,519
You literally cut me off
and parked in me bay!

220
00:12:00,520 --> 00:12:02,239
This ain't...
Nobody said...

221
00:12:02,240 --> 00:12:04,359
That's yours,
that's his, that's mine!

222
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:06,079
Nobody said, "That's my bay."

223
00:12:06,080 --> 00:12:07,239
They did...

224
00:12:07,240 --> 00:12:09,919
Now, at this point,
it was suggested to us that,

225
00:12:09,920 --> 00:12:12,919
if we were ever to become
real-life HGV drivers,

226
00:12:12,920 --> 00:12:16,479
we should probably get
a few lessons,

227
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:21,039
so we all booked in on
an intensive training course,

228
00:12:21,040 --> 00:12:25,680
and set out to get our licences
as soon as possible.

229
00:12:47,400 --> 00:12:49,079
Oh, yes!

230
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:53,080
One qualified truck driver
at your service.

231
00:12:56,960 --> 00:13:00,479
You are now looking
at a graduate from

232
00:13:00,480 --> 00:13:04,680
